,\n      \"totalTokens\": 22609,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 3.7082245000000005,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1775869200569,\n      \"endedAt\": 1775869218270,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 17701,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\ares\\\\sessions\\\\8e2d6331-a8f3-48ba-8ea2-d13daa94eb4a.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"**Checking task status**\\n\\nI’ve noticed there are only two old tasks completed, which might not require any action right now. However, it might be smart to consider a broader query around the Smart Project area. Maybe focusing on specific areas or properties will yield more insight. I could check if any open task is assigned to Ares or look at the domain, making sure to filter out tasks that are marked as \\\"Done.\\\"\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_4Zq1bWeVn9PVZjlrGFzMCCxG|fc_0b08366c1599455a0169dd91bd9dac8191acff417122e66515\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"command\": \"$headers = @{ 'Authorization' = \\\"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\\\"; 'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'; 'Content-Type' = 'application/json' }\\n$body = @{ filter = @{ property='Status'; status=@{ does_not_equal='Done' } }; page_size = 100 } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10\\n$r = Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri 'https://api.notion.com/v1/databases/32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7/query' -Headers $headers -Body $body\\n$r.results | ForEach-Object {\\n  $p=$_.properties\\n  [PSCustomObject]@{\\n    Task=($p.'Task name'.title.plain_text -join '')\\n    Status=if($p.Status.status){$p.Status.status.name}else{''}\\n    Priority=if($p.Priority.select){$p.Priority.select.name}else{''}\\n    Area=($p.Area.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\n    Owner=($p.Owner.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\n    NextCheck=if($p.'Next check'.date){$p.'Next check'.date.start}else{''}\\n    NextStep=($p.'Next step'.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\n    Due=if($p.Deadline.date){$p.Deadline.date.start}else{''}\\n  }\\n} | Sort-Object Priority,Status | Format-Table -AutoSize | Out-String -Width 260\",\n                \"workdir\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace-ares\",\n                \"yieldMs\": 10000,\n                \"timeout\": 30\n              },\n              \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"$headers = @{ 'Authorization' = \\\\\\\"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\\\\\\\"; 'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'; 'Content-Type' = 'application/json' }\\\\n$body = @{ filter = @{ property='Status'; status=@{ does_not_equal='Done' } }; page_size = 100 } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10\\\\n$r = Invoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri 'https://api.notion.com/v1/databases/32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7/query' -Headers $headers -Body $body\\\\n$r.results | ForEach-Object {\\\\n  $p=$_.properties\\\\n  [PSCustomObject]@{\\\\n    Task=($p.'Task name'.title.plain_text -join '')\\\\n    Status=if($p.Status.status){$p.Status.status.name}else{''}\\\\n    Priority=if($p.Priority.select){$p.Priority.select.name}else{''}\\\\n    Area=($p.Area.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\\\n    Owner=($p.Owner.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\\\n    NextCheck=if($p.'Next check'.date){$p.'Next check'.date.start}else{''}\\\\n    NextStep=($p.'Next step'.rich_text.plain_text -join '')\\\\n    Due=if($p.Deadline.date){$p.Deadline.date.start}else{''}\\\\n  }\\\\n} | Sort-Object Priority,Status | Format-Table -AutoSize | Out-String -Width 260\\\",\\\"workdir\\\":\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\Gustavo\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace-ares\\\",\\\"yieldMs\\\":10000,\\\"timeout\\\":30}\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n          \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n          \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 242,\n            \"output\": 446,\n            \"totalTokens\": 22192,\n            \"cacheRead\": 21504,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.012670999999999998\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776128436343,\n          \"responseId\": \"resp_0b08366c1599455a0169dd91b7fa1c819190094814d00c88a4\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"5fe9a06f\",\n            \"seq\": 14\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating training routines**\\n\\nIt seems like there are no current tasks, and I’m thinking about Monday not being a training day based on the routine, which is Wednesday, Thursday, Saturday, and Sunday. So, today might be a recovery day instead. I’m also wondering if I should follow up with the group to see if they trained, but I don't have any recent context to guide me. According to instructions, I might just need to confirm: HEARTBEAT_OK.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"HEARTBEAT_OK\",\n              \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0b08366c1599455a0169dd91c8cf8c81918eedd223c8888136\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n          \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n          \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 593,\n            \"output\": 86,\n            \"totalTokens\": 22695,\n            \"cacheRead\": 22016,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.0082765\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776128447070,\n          \"responseId\": \"resp_0b08366c1599455a0169dd91c28f0081918fdcaec62b79f525\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"1986502f\",\n            \"seq\": 16\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":9,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:main:whatsapp:direct:+573183718246","kind":"other","channel":"whatsapp","displayName":"+573183718246","deliveryContext":{"channel":"whatsapp","to":"+573183718246","accountId":"default"},"updatedAt":1776130053930,"sessionId":"f42459b9-34a7-400d-b6b5-f06d090a0700","model":"gpt-5.4","contextTokens":272000,"totalTokens":90336,"estimatedCostUsd":1.470899,"status":"running","startedAt":1776130053914,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"whatsapp","lastTo":"+573183718246","lastAccountId":"default","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\f42459b9-34a7-400d-b6b5-f06d090a0700.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Puedo dejarle el grupo, pero **yo no puedo crear un grupo de WhatsApp desde aquí** como si tocara la app. Lo que sí hago es dejar todo listo para que ese grupo caiga en **Prisma** apenas exista.\n\nNecesito una de estas dos:\n- **me pasas el nombre exacto del grupo** y después escribes cualquier mensaje ahí para detectar el `group-jid`, o\n- **creas el grupo** y me reenvías un mensaje desde ese grupo\n\nCon eso yo hago:\n- binding del grupo → `prisma`\n- activación por nombre (`Prisma`)\n- prueba de routing\n\nSi quieres, hazlo así de una:\n1. crea el grupo\n2. mete el mismo número de WhatsApp conectado\n3. manda un mensaje tipo: **“Prisma hola”**\n4. yo termino el routing aquí\n\nSi quieres, también te propongo nombre para el grupo.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_074be59d93eb32710169dd97ae6624819198565ea7af13568f\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"text","text":" Puedo dejarle el grupo, pero **yo no puedo crear un grupo de WhatsApp desde aquí** como si tocara la app. Lo que sí hago es dejar todo listo para que ese grupo caiga en **Prisma** apenas exista.\n\nNecesito una de estas dos:\n- me pasas el **nombre exacto del grupo** y luego escribes ahí para detectar el grupo, o\n- **creas el grupo** y me reenvías un mensaje desde ese grupo\n\nCon eso yo hago:\n- binding del grupo → `prisma`\n- activación por nombre (`Prisma`)\n- prueba de routing\n\nHazlo así y lo cierro:\n1. crea el grupo\n2. mete el mismo número conectado\n3. manda un mensaje tipo: **“Prisma hola”**\n4. yo termino el routing aquí\n\nSi quieres, también te propongo nombre para el grupo.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_074be59d93eb32710169dd97b31cbc81919a50c734c89aa1fe\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1248,"output":391,"totalTokens":90727,"cacheRead":89088,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0.031257}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776129943289,"responseId":"resp_074be59d93eb32710169dd979b77348191b8fd0e66c6a4a1a0","__openclaw":{"id":"18bc4af3","seq":86}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ya"}],"timestamp":1776130053913,"__openclaw":{"id":"23379012","seq":87},"senderLabel":"Gustavo Toledo (+573183718246)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a detectar el grupo recién creado desde sesiones/logs y dejar el routing de Prisma listo.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_074be59d93eb32710169dd98101850819186c4dbf9449a6bff\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4fvr9ErHFAcEawTzSUMEtLCW|fc_074be59d93eb32710169dd98131dac81919c31e516c04da75a","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["agent"],"limit":20,"activeMinutes":60,"messageLimit":3},"partialJson":"{\"kinds\":[\"agent\"],\"limit\":20,\"activeMinutes\":60,\"messageLimit\":3}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yOtidBJAnOXEZWLLcYmsWWkC|fc_074be59d93eb32710169dd98131dc481919189d167efa73584","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content -Tail 200 \"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\logs\\gateway.log\"","